    "body": "This commit fixes the file write operation in ColumnFamilyStore by using a try-with-resources statement to ensure that the PrintStream is properly closed. This change addresses potential issues with file handling and improves the overall robustness of the code."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Fix NullPointerException in BigTableScanner.close()",
    "body": "This commit fixes a NullPointerException in BigTableScanner.close() by introducing atomic closure of input/output streams. The issue was identified as CASSANDRA-9531 and was caused by the segment being desallocated before its close method was called. The fix ensures that the file input/output streams are properly closed, preventing the NullPointerException from occurring."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Fix SSTableReader to handle downsampled index summaries",
    "body": "This commit fixes the SSTableReader to correctly handle downsampled index summaries. The method load() now checks for an index summary that was downsampled even though the serialization format doesn't support that. If it was downsampled, it rebuilds it. This fix addresses the issue described in CASSANDRA-8993."
